div.p:
               Lord Chief Iustice. There was hardly ever any Book more pernicious
to set us together by the Ears than this, nor any thing a greater Incendiary;
One can hardly write a worse—

So that, your Hopes of any thing of that kind, will be vain;
for all the Judges have declared this Offence, at the Common-Law,
to be Punishable in the Seller, though in the way of his
Trade: The Books may be seized, and the Person punished.
